{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Centrosome-associated protein 350 (CEP350 or CAP350) plays an essential role in centriole growth by stabilising a procentriolar seed composed of, at least, SASS6 and CENPJ [[cite:PUB00069164]]. It is required for anchoring microtubules to the centrosomes and for the integrity of the microtubule network [[cite:PUB00069685]]. It also stabilises Golgi-associated microtubules and maintains a continuous pericentrosomal Golgi ribbon [[cite:PUB00069166]].\nCEP350 possesses a CAP-Gly domain which is targeted to the centrosome or the Golgi-like network and binds microtubules through an N-terminal basic region [[cite:PUB00069166]].</p>\n\n<p>This family also includes the coiled-coil domain-containing protein 187 (CC187), a centrosomal protein whose function is still unknown.</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR13958" "CENTROSOME-ASSOCIATED PROTEIN 350"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Centrosome-associated protein 350/Coiled-coil domain-containing protein 187", "short" "CEP350/CC187"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 1, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 887, "taxa" 3573, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 3093, "sets" 0, "proteins" 3093, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 935}, "pathways" 1}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR028750", :literature {"PUB00069164" {"URL" nil, "issue" "Pt 1", "authors" ["Patel H" "Truant R" "Rachubinski RA" "Capone JP."], "ISO_journal" "J. Cell. Sci.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1242/jcs.01600", "medline_journal" "J Cell Sci", "title" "Activity and subcellular compartmentalization of peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor alpha are altered by the centrosome-associated protein CAP350.", "year" 2005, "raw_pages" "175-86", "volume" "118", "ISBN" nil, "PMID" 15615782}, "P